reviews.review_text:
nice new version of a great show! Great sounding recording of this fantastic show.  This recording has more umph than the rest, bordering on distortion at times.  But it also has a great "soundscape", feels wide open and fills the whole screen - so to speak.  The biggest plus is the complete Good Lovin'.  Since the second set is long and uninterrupted most others have the ending cut and patched with a not so good sounding patch, this version has the whole burrito but it just makes it just to the end, no Bobby saying goodnight. 
 
The patches that are used are mostly seamless.

In '83 they were doing extended IKYR jams.  In this one Jerry does 3 rounds for each solo.  

There are a few tunes where only one or two versions are worth repeat listens, this show has two of those:  Throwing Stones and Good Lovin'.  No other version of either song stand out among the 150 shows I saw like these two do, just like the 3/27/87 Touch of Grey.  

Once in a while you can get shown the light!

AUD Recordings of 1983 Thanks to Chris & Rango, We have these amazing aud recordings of the dead at there 80s peak 1983! I love SBDs but these guys did an amazing job of capturing the boy's before it got popular to be a dead head. back before tapers had a taping section in 84'
